Continue Refactoring: Microservice Extraction Plan
Service Boundaries
Execution Service
Purpose: Handle /api/execute orchestration start (LangGraph/StepQueue), execution lifecycle.
Owns: Execution creation, failure handling, resume kickoffs.
Sessions Service
Purpose: Pause/resume flows, checkpointing, resume prompts/answers normalization.
Owns: Pause/resume endpoints and session state transitions.
Progress Service
Purpose: Progress stream (SSE) + snapshots.
Owns: openProgressStream, getProgress read path; single source of truth for progress.
Runner Service
Purpose: Sandboxed test execution.
Owns: runInSandbox, install deps, detect command.
Planning Service
Purpose: Task decomposition + per-subtask execution helpers.
Owns: planning endpoints if separated, or stay internal to Execution.
Files/Status Service
Purpose: Health, executions lookup, output archives, file listing/serving.
Fixtures/Replay Service
Purpose: Read fixtures, replay repair/subtasks for debugging.
Orchestrator Service
Purpose: State machine, checkpoints, workspace manifest, job queue, abort signals.
Owns: execution/session state and transitions (single source of truth).
Notes:

Keep current REST surface identical initially (gateway/back-compat), then introduce versioned service endpoints under /v1/... when split behind an API gateway or shared router.
API Contract Design (v1 sketch)
Execution Service
POST /api/execute → { ok, executionId, sessionId, ... }
GET /api/executions/:id → { ok, execution }
Sessions Service
POST /api/sessions/:id/pause → { ok, paused: true }
POST /api/sessions/:id/resume → { ok, resumed: true }
Progress Service
GET /api/progress/:sessionId/stream (SSE)
GET /api/progress/:sessionId → { ok, stage, progress, state, paused }
Runner Service
POST /api/run-tests → { status, passCount, failCount, durationMs, logsPath }
Files/Status Service
GET /healthz → 200
GET /output-archive/:project?format=zip|tar
GET /output/:project/*
GET /api/files/:project/:path(*)
Fixtures/Replay Service
GET /api/fixtures/:project
POST /api/replay/repair | /api/replay/subtask → replay results
Design:

Use RFC 9457 problem+json for error responses consistently.
Version with headers or path (/v1/...) when moving behind gateway.
JSON Schemas live under contracts/schemas/* (no breaking changes).
Data Separation
Extract in-memory maps (progressSessions, orchestrationSessions) into the Orchestrator Service.
Single source of truth: Orchestrator persists checkpoints and session/execution state (disk or Redis in future phases).
Other services access state via Orchestrator API (no direct shared memory).
Files/Status service remains read-only over output dir.
Dependency Management
Service discovery via environment variables:
EXECUTION_URL, SESSIONS_URL, PROGRESS_URL, RUNNER_URL, FILES_URL, FIXTURES_URL, ORCHESTRATOR_URL
Keep internal clients typed and minimal; retry with backoff and deadlines.
No new dependencies until explicitly approved; reuse existing HTTP utilities.
Error Handling
Standardize on:
Timeouts (per call, e.g., 3–10s)
Retries (idempotent endpoints only, e.g., GET; controlled retries for POST with idempotency keys)
RFC 9457 problem+json responses
Map internal errors to stable public problem types.
